OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision) is a popular open-source library that provides a wide range of tools and functions for computer vision and image processing applications. It is widely used in various real-time applications across different fields. Here are some examples of real-time applications of OpenCV:

1) Face Detection and Recognition: OpenCV can be used to detect and recognize faces in real-time, enabling applications like facial authentication, access control systems, and emotion recognition.

2) Object Detection and Tracking: OpenCV can be used to detect and track objects in real-time, enabling applications like surveillance, autonomous vehicles, and augmented reality.

3) Gesture Recognition: OpenCV can be used to recognize hand gestures in real-time, enabling applications like sign language interpretation and gesture-based user interfaces.

4) Lane Detection and Autonomous Driving: OpenCV can be used to detect lane markings on roads in real-time, which is a critical component of autonomous driving systems.

5) Image and Video Filtering: OpenCV provides various image and video filtering techniques that can be applied in real-time, such as blurring, edge detection, and color manipulation, useful for real-time video enhancement and special effects.

6)Augmented Reality (AR): OpenCV can be used to overlay virtual objects onto the real world in real-time, creating interactive AR experiences.

7) Robotics: OpenCV can be used in robotics for tasks like object detection, obstacle avoidance, and visual SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) to help robots perceive and interact with their environment in real-time.

8) Medical Imaging: OpenCV can be used in real-time medical imaging applications, such as detecting and tracking anomalies in live medical scans like X-rays and ultrasounds.

9) Biometrics: OpenCV can be utilized in real-time biometric applications, such as fingerprint recognition and iris scanning.

10) Motion Tracking: OpenCV can be used to track the movement of objects or people in real-time, useful for security systems and sports analysis.